# ClawGame License

**Version 1.1**

## Summary

ClawGame is **free to use** for individuals, hobbyists, and small businesses with **annual revenue under $100,000 USD**. Redistribution of ClawGame as a product is prohibited without a commercial license.

---

## Free Use (Revenue < $100k/year)

You may use ClawGame **free of charge** if you are:

- An individual developer
- A hobbyist or indie game developer
- A company, studio, or organization with **annual gross revenue under $100,000 USD**

### Free Use Rights

Under the free tier, you may:

- ✅ Use ClawGame to create and publish games
- ✅ Modify the source code for your own use
- ✅ Distribute games you create with ClawGame (royalty-free)
- ✅ Fork the repository for personal/internal use
- ✅ Host ClawGame on your own server for your own use
- ✅ Self-host for your team or organization (if under $100k revenue)

### Free Use Restrictions

- ❌ **You may NOT redistribute ClawGame as a product** (modified or unmodified)
- ❌ You may not sell, sublicense, or resell ClawGame
- ❌ You may not host ClawGame as a service for others (SaaS)
- ❌ You may not use ClawGame as part of a competing product
- ❌ You may not remove or alter license notices

### Attribution Requirement

You must include attribution in games you publish: "Made with ClawGame" with a link to https://github.com/pgedeon/ClawGame

---

## Commercial License (Revenue ≥ $100k/year OR Redistribution)

A **Commercial License** is required if:

- Your company has **annual gross revenue of $100,000 USD or more**, OR
- You want to **redistribute ClawGame as a product** in any form, OR
- You want to **host ClawGame as a service for others** (SaaS)

### Commercial License Benefits

- Full commercial rights
- Redistribution rights (white-label, SaaS, embedded, etc.)
- Host as a service for customers
- Priority support
- No attribution required
- Access to enterprise features (when available)

### Obtaining a Commercial License

Contact: **clawgame@pgedeon.com**

---

## Open Source Contributions

Contributions to ClawGame are welcome! By submitting a pull request, you:

1. Grant the project maintainers a perpetual, worldwide, non-exclusive license to use your contribution
2. Agree that your contribution will be licensed under these same terms
3. Confirm you have the right to grant these licenses

---

## Definitions

- **"ClawGame"** refers to the software, source code, and all associated files
- **"Redistribute"** means to share, publish, sell, or make available ClawGame as a product to third parties
- **"Self-host"** means running ClawGame on your own infrastructure for your own use
- **"SaaS"** means hosting ClawGame as a service available to third parties
- **"Use"** means running, modifying, or building upon ClawGame for your own purposes
- **"Revenue"** means annual gross revenue (total income before expenses) of your company or organization

